'''Arthur Gordon Butchers''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|size=85%}} (11 February 1885 &ndash; 21 April 1960) was a New Zealand principal, educationalist and historian. He was born in [[Brunswick, Victoria|Brunswick]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]] on 11 February 1885.<ref name="DNZB Butchers">{{DNZB|last=Arnold|first=Rollo|id=4b53|title=Arthur Gordon Butchers|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

In the [[1947 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|1947 New Year Honours]], Butchers was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] in recognition of his service as headmaster of [[The Correspondence School]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue= 37836 |date=1 January 1947 |page=32 |supp=y }}</ref>

